{
  "schemaVersion": 1,
  "unitId": "b2.2/unit-05-indefinites-prefixes",
  "passThreshold": 0.7,
  "exercises": [
    {
      "id": "ex-mc-1",
      "type": "multiple-choice",
      "skill": "writing",
      "prompt": "Formal 'whoever': « ___ connaît notre histoire comprendra. »",
      "options": [
        {
          "id": "a",
          "text": "Quiconque"
        },
        {
          "id": "b",
          "text": "Quelconque"
        },
        {
          "id": "c",
          "text": "N'importe quoi"
        }
      ],
      "correct": [
        "a"
      ],
      "explanation": "Quiconque = whoever (formal subject pronoun). Quelconque is an adjective."
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-mc-2",
      "type": "multiple-choice",
      "skill": "reading",
      "prompt": "« Un film très quelconque » means the film is…",
      "options": [
        {
          "id": "a",
          "text": "mediocre / ordinary"
        },
        {
          "id": "b",
          "text": "outstanding"
        },
        {
          "id": "c",
          "text": "unknown"
        }
      ],
      "correct": [
        "a"
      ],
      "explanation": "After the noun with très, quelconque = unremarkable, mediocre."
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-fb-1",
      "type": "fill-blank",
      "skill": "writing",
      "prompt": "Nonsense alert!",
      "inputMode": "dropdown",
      "template": "Ne l'écoute pas, il dit {{b1}} !",
      "blanks": [
        {
          "id": "b1",
          "accept": [
            "n'importe quoi"
          ],
          "options": [
            "n'importe quoi",
            "n'importe qui",
            "quiconque"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "explanation": "Dire n'importe quoi = to talk nonsense."
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-fb-2",
      "type": "fill-blank",
      "skill": "writing",
      "prompt": "All, everything or everyone?",
      "inputMode": "dropdown",
      "template": "{{b1}} les élus régionaux ont signé la déclaration.",
      "blanks": [
        {
          "id": "b1",
          "accept": [
            "Tous"
          ],
          "options": [
            "Tous",
            "Tout",
            "Tout le monde"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "explanation": "Before les + plural noun → tous: tous les élus."
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-mc-3",
      "type": "multiple-choice",
      "skill": "writing",
      "prompt": "Build the opposite of « honnête »:",
      "options": [
        {
          "id": "a",
          "text": "malhonnête"
        },
        {
          "id": "b",
          "text": "inhonnête"
        },
        {
          "id": "c",
          "text": "déshonnête"
        }
      ],
      "correct": [
        "a"
      ],
      "explanation": "Honnête takes mal-: malhonnête. Each word has its own prefix — learn them as pairs."
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-fb-3",
      "type": "fill-blank",
      "skill": "writing",
      "prompt": "Build the opposite of « régulier » (one word).",
      "inputMode": "typed",
      "template": "Des horaires {{b1}} compliquent la vie des salariés.",
      "blanks": [
        {
          "id": "b1",
          "accept": [
            "irréguliers",
            "irreguliers"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "explanation": "Before r-, the prefix is ir-: irrégulier(s)."
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-mp-1",
      "type": "match-pairs",
      "skill": "reading",
      "prompt": "Match each word to its prefixed opposite.",
      "pairs": [
        {
          "id": "p1",
          "left": "connu",
          "right": "inconnu"
        },
        {
          "id": "p2",
          "left": "content",
          "right": "mécontent"
        },
        {
          "id": "p3",
          "left": "agréable",
          "right": "désagréable"
        },
        {
          "id": "p4",
          "left": "légal",
          "right": "illégal"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-ro-1",
      "type": "reorder",
      "skill": "writing",
      "prompt": "Put the words in order: \"Anyone can join the association.\"",
      "tokens": [
        {
          "id": "t1",
          "text": "N'importe qui"
        },
        {
          "id": "t2",
          "text": "peut"
        },
        {
          "id": "t3",
          "text": "adhérer"
        },
        {
          "id": "t4",
          "text": "à"
        },
        {
          "id": "t5",
          "text": "l'association"
        }
      ],
      "correctOrder": [
        "t1",
        "t2",
        "t3",
        "t4",
        "t5"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-li-1",
      "type": "listen",
      "skill": "listening",
      "prompt": "Listen to the council speech. What intensity of disagreement is this?",
      "audio": "audio/b2.2/unit-05-indefinites-prefixes/listen-1.mp3",
      "transcript": "Nous contestons cette décision malhonnête et nous réclamons un nouveau vote.",
      "options": [
        {
          "id": "a",
          "text": "Strong: they dispute the decision and demand a new vote"
        },
        {
          "id": "b",
          "text": "Mild: they politely express a small doubt"
        },
        {
          "id": "c",
          "text": "None: they fully agree with the decision"
        }
      ],
      "correct": [
        "a"
      ],
      "explanation": "Contester + réclamer = opposition directe + revendication, the strong end of the scale."
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-rd-1",
      "type": "read",
      "skill": "reading",
      "prompt": "Read the open letter and answer both questions.",
      "passageFr": "Quiconque aime nos régions le sait : nos langues régionales ne sont pas des folklores quelconques. Tout le monde peut apprendre le breton, à n'importe quel âge. Nous nous opposons donc à la fermeture des classes bilingues — une décision incompréhensible et, selon nos avocats, illégale. Nous réclamons son annulation.",
      "passageEn": "Whoever loves our regions knows it: our regional languages are not just any folklore. Everyone can learn Breton, at any age. We therefore oppose the closure of the bilingual classes — an incomprehensible and, according to our lawyers, illegal decision. We demand its cancellation.",
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "q1",
          "prompt": "What do the writers oppose?",
          "options": [
            {
              "id": "a",
              "text": "The closure of bilingual classes"
            },
            {
              "id": "b",
              "text": "The teaching of Breton"
            },
            {
              "id": "c",
              "text": "Learning at any age"
            }
          ],
          "correct": [
            "a"
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "q2",
          "prompt": "Which two prefixed opposites describe the decision?",
          "options": [
            {
              "id": "a",
              "text": "incompréhensible and illégale"
            },
            {
              "id": "b",
              "text": "malhonnête and désagréable"
            },
            {
              "id": "c",
              "text": "inconnue and irrégulière"
            }
          ],
          "correct": [
            "a"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ex-mc-4",
      "type": "multiple-choice",
      "skill": "writing",
      "prompt": "Any time at all: « Appelle-moi à ___ heure. »",
      "options": [
        {
          "id": "a",
          "text": "n'importe quelle"
        },
        {
          "id": "b",
          "text": "n'importe qui"
        },
        {
          "id": "c",
          "text": "quiconque"
        }
      ],
      "correct": [
        "a"
      ],
      "explanation": "Before a noun → n'importe quel(le): à n'importe quelle heure."
    },
